+# =============================================================================
+# Zephyr Lux — environment variables (canonical reference)
+# =============================================================================
+# Copy values into `.env.local` (gitignored) for Vite, and set the same names in
+# the Vercel project (or your shell) for `vercel dev` + deployed API routes.
+#
+# Security (FR-PAY-001, NFR-SEC-002): Never put STRIPE_SECRET_KEY, STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET,
+# VERCEL_BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN, RESEND_API_KEY, or any Supabase service role key in a
+# VITE_* variable or client code. Only Stripe publishable keys (pk_...) belong in
+# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY.
+# =============================================================================
+
+# --- Server (Vercel / Node / `vercel dev`) — read in api/_lib/env.ts ---------
+# `VERCEL_BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN` is mapped to `ENV.VERCEL_BLOB_RW_TOKEN` in code.
+#
+# SUPABASE_URL: required for Epic 4 checkout + webhooks (pending orders, payment_events, paid order reads).
+# Use the same project URL as VITE_SUPABASE_URL if you already set it for the catalog.
+#SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
+#
+# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: required with SUPABASE_URL for api/create-payment-intent, api/stripe-webhook,
+# and api/order-by-payment-intent. Server only — never in VITE_* or the browser.
+#SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
+#
+# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: optional server alias for the public anon key; used by api/admin-order-fulfillment
+# to verify admin JWTs (same value as VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY). If unset, the handler falls back to VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in local `.env`.
+#SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
+#
+# ENABLE_CUSTOMER_SHIPMENT_NOTIFICATION: optional. `true` / `1` / `yes` turns on customer “shipped” email from api/admin-order-fulfillment (Story 5-6; needs Resend + templates). Omit or false for fulfillment-only (5-4 default).
+#ENABLE_CUSTOMER_SHIPMENT_NOTIFICATION=true
+
+# NODE_ENV: optional. Default: "development". Used for store backend auto-selection.
+#NODE_ENV=development
+
+# FRONTEND_URL: optional. Server-side CORS for PaymentIntent API, redirects, and transactional links
+# in email handlers (Epic 4+, Epic 7 order lookup emails). Match the storefront origin customers use.
+# Use the SAME canonical hostname as `VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` in each environment — FRONTEND_URL is server-only;
+# `VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` is client-only for Open Graph/meta (see Story 7-2 epic follow-ups).
+# (local: http://localhost:5173, preview: your *.vercel.app URL, production: https://yourdomain).
+# Default in code if unset: http://localhost:5173
+#FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
+#
+# DEV_API_PROXY: optional. For `npm run dev` (Vite), `/api` is proxied to this origin
+# (default http://127.0.0.1:3000) so the SPA can `fetch("/api/...")`. Point it at
+# `vercel dev` (or match `concurrently` / `dev:full` if you use a different port).
+#DEV_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:3000
+
+# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY: required for real payments & webhooks. Server only. e.g. sk_test_... (local/preview) or sk_live_... (production)
+#STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxxxxxxx
+
+# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET: required to verify webhooks. Server only. From Stripe CLI or Dashboard.
+#STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxxxxx
+
+# RESEND_API_KEY: optional. Transactional email when wired. Server only.
+#RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxxxxxx
+#
+# RESEND_FROM: required for real sends — must be a verified domain/sender in the Resend dashboard
+# (sandbox: use their docs for test addresses; production: your domain DNS verified).
+#RESEND_FROM="Zephyr Lux <orders@mail.yourdomain.com>"
+#
+# SUPPORT_EMAIL and CONTACT_EMAIL: optional (CONTACT_EMAIL is an alias for SUPPORT_EMAIL).
+# Shown in customer order confirmation (E4-S6) when set; otherwise copy falls back to RESEND_FROM.
+#SUPPORT_EMAIL=help@yourdomain.com
+#
+# OWNER_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL: optional. Comma-separated inboxes for "new paid order" owner alerts (Epic 4 E4-S5). Server only.
+# Without RESEND_API_KEY + RESEND_FROM + this recipient, paid orders still complete but owner email is skipped (warn logged).
+#OWNER_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL=you@yourdomain.com
+
+# STORE_BACKEND: optional. auto | blob | local — controls order/blob storage. Default: auto
+#STORE_BACKEND=auto
+
+# VERCEL_BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN: optional in dev; used when persisting to Vercel Blob. Server only.
+#VERCEL_BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=vercel_blob_rw_xxxxxxxx
+
+# LOG_LEVEL: optional. pino log level. Default: info
+#LOG_LEVEL=info
+
+# --- Client (Vite) — only VITE_* is exposed to the browser -------------------
+# VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL: optional but recommended for production Open Graph / JSON-LD absolute URLs.
+# Must be the origin customers use (e.g. local: http://localhost:5173, production: https://www.yourstore.com).
+# No trailing slash. Read: src/seo/site.ts
+#VITE_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://www.example.com
+
+# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY: optional. If set, loadStripe() runs on checkout. Use pk_test_... / pk_live_... only.
+# Read: src/components/Cart/CheckoutPage.tsx (legacy duplicate: CheckoutPage.js)
+#VITE_STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_test_xxxxxxxx
+
+# VITE_USE_MOCK_STRIPE: optional. "true" enables mock payment path. Default: unset / false
+# Read: src/utils/config.ts (legacy: config.js)
+#VITE_USE_MOCK_STRIPE=true
+
+# VITE_API_URL: optional. Subscription/newsletter API base. Default in code if unset: http://localhost:5000
+# Read: src/components/SubscriptionForm/SubscriptionForm.tsx (legacy: SubscriptionForm.js)
+# For `npm run dev:full`, set this to the origin shown by `vercel dev` (often http://localhost:3000), not blindly to the code default.
+#VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
+
+# VITE_CATALOG_BACKEND: optional. "supabase" uses SupabaseCatalogAdapter; anything else = static JSON.
+# Read: src/catalog/adapter.ts
+#VITE_CATALOG_BACKEND=static
+
+# VITE_SUPABASE_URL: required when VITE_CATALOG_BACKEND=supabase. Public project URL (https://….supabase.co).
+# Read: src/catalog/adapter.ts
+#VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
+
+# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: required when VITE_CATALOG_BACKEND=supabase. Public anon key (RLS-enforced); safe in the browser bundle.
+# Read: src/catalog/adapter.ts
+#VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
+
+# --- Analytics (Story 6-6, FR-AN-002) — optional; omit in prod for no third-party calls --------
+# Events are privacy-scoped (pathname-only page_view, no Stripe IDs / email in payloads). With both
+# variables unset, production builds no-op analytics (no console spam); dev uses console.debug only.
+# Pick ONE provider path:
+# - Plausible: set domain and add Plausible script so `window.plausible` exists.
+# - GA4: set measurement ID and load gtag.js so `window.gtag` exists.
+#VITE_ANALYTICS_PLAUSIBLE_DOMAIN=yourdomain.com
+#VITE_ANALYTICS_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXX
+
+# Admin (story 2-6): same VITE_SUPABASE_* powers Supabase Auth for /admin/* (src/lib/supabaseBrowser.ts).
+# Catalog writes require app_metadata.role = "admin" on the user JWT: Supabase Dashboard → Authentication →
+# Users → select user → App metadata (raw JSON), e.g. { "role": "admin" }.
+# Optional server-only supplement (never the sole production gate): ALLOWED_ADMIN_EMAILS in api/admin/* if added later.
+
+# --- Server-only / reserved names ---------------------------------------------
+# Epic 4: create-payment-intent, stripe-webhook, and order-by-payment-intent require SUPABASE_URL +
+# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY (see top of this file). Without them, checkout and webhooks return 503.
+# Never expose the service role key in VITE_* or client code (NFR-SEC-002).
+# TRANSACTIONAL_EMAIL_API_KEY= # example reserved name if email is abstracted / renamed from RESEND_API_KEY; server-only
+# (Additional provider keys as named in PRD / architecture when implemented.)
+#
+# Before enabling customer/owner Resend in production: set RESEND_API_KEY, RESEND_FROM (verified),
+# SUPPORT_EMAIL for human-facing support, and owner inbox OWNER_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL (E4-S5) if used.
